
  Using the Shellduino Skeleton
  =============================

  Getting Shellduino:
  -------------------

  1. Get shellduino-skel
     $ git clone git://github.com/frickel/shellduino-skel.git

  2.  Copy skeleton to your project directory (e.g. hello)
     $ cp -r shellduino-skel /home/fnord/projects/hello

  3. Change your local work directory to your project directory
     $ cd /home/fnord/projects/hello

  4. Change some settings in 'Makefile'
     TARGET = hello

     Sometimes you've got to change the MCU-Type (e.g. m168, m328p,..).
     (See *duino guide).


  Building:
  ---------

  1. Change your local work directory to your project directory
     $ cd /home/fnord/projects/hello

  2. To compile your project, type: 
     $ make 

  3. Writing the .hex flash-image to the *duino:
     $ make flash

